#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:3
msgid "Response Guide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:5
msgid ""
"This is a :doc:`Code of Conduct<CodeOfConduct>` (CoC) incident response "
"guide used by the Code of Conduct Committee and LLVM event organizers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:9
msgid "Code of Conduct Committee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:11
msgid ""
"All responses to Code of Conduct reports will be managed by a Code of "
"Conduct Committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:15
msgid "Additional Code of Conduct Response Teams"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:17
msgid ""
"In-person events will have an additional response team to immediately "
"respond to an incident. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:20
msgid "Each LLVM Developers' Meeting has a Code of Conduct response team."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:21
msgid ""
"For LLVM meetups, the local organizers will be the first point of contact."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:22
msgid ""
"Any other event funded by the LLVM Foundation or listed on the LLVM website, "
"will have a code of conduct response team or point of contact for CoC "
"reports."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:26
msgid ""
"These teams should determine if an :ref:`immediate response<Immediate "
"Response Checklist>` is needed before sending the report to the Code of "
"Conduct committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:33
msgid "Receiving a Report"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:35
msgid ""
"Reports are typically received by email (conduct@llvm.org) or in person from "
"the reporter or event CoC response team."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:38
msgid ""
"When receiving a report by email, the CoC Committee should acknowledge "
"receipt within 24 hours.  The acknowledgement should be understanding and "
"compassionate but no commitment should be made on whether this is a "
"violation or which action will be taken. Specific guidance is in the "
"checklist below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:43
msgid ""
"For in-person events that have a violation reported, the report should be "
"sent to the Code of Conduct committee within 24 hours by the on-site CoC "
"response team."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:51
msgid "Immediate Response Checklist"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:53
msgid ""
"The CoC committee generally works, decides, and communicates together. If "
"the report indicates that an immediate response is required and other "
"committee members are not available, any committee member may take the "
"immediate action they think is necessary. In-person Code of Conduct response "
"teams should use this checklist to determine if an immediate response is "
"needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:59
msgid ""
"If the incident involves physical danger, contact the appropriate law "
"enforcement or event security immediately. Ensure the reporter feels safe "
"and stay with them if possible until help arrives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:62
msgid ""
"If the act is ongoing and involves harassment or threats against someone in "
"any space (online or physical), any appropriate response (e.g., ban, "
"physical removal, or moderation) may be used to immediately stop it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:65
msgid ""
"For events that include talks, organizers should end talks early if the "
"violations include harassment or violent threats. There may be talks where "
"other types of code of conduct violations occur and organizers should do "
"their best to determine if a talk should be ended early or not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:70
msgid ""
"When undertaking an immediate response, document the action and notify the "
"committee within 24 hours."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:75
msgid "Response Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:77
msgid ""
"The following is a summary of the steps the committee takes when responding "
"to a reported incident."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:80
msgid ""
"Determine if there is a need for an :ref:`immediate response<Immediate "
"Response Checklist>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:83
msgid ":ref:`Acknowledge the report<Receiving a report>` within 24 hours."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:85
msgid ""
":ref:`Discuss the incident report<Incident Response Assessment>`, gather "
"more information, and determine a :ref:`resolution<Resolutions>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:88
msgid ""
"During this process, the :ref:`reporter will be informed of the "
"resolution<Following Up With the Reportee>` and feedback is requested. This "
"feedback may or may not be used to re-evaluate the resolution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:92
msgid ""
"Inform the reportee of the resolution. The reportee is provided options to :"
"ref:`appeal<Appeal Process>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:95
msgid "The :ref:`resolution<Resolutions>` is implemented."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:97
msgid ""
"All reports, data, notes, and resolutions are logged in a private location "
"(e.g., Google Drive or other database)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:100
msgid ""
"The committee will never make public statements about a resolution and will "
"only publish :ref:`transparency reports<Transparency Reports>`. If a public "
"statement is necessary and requested by the committee, it will be given by "
"the LLVM Foundation Board of Directors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:106
msgid "Report Acknowledgement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:108
msgid ""
"When a report is received, the committee will reply to the reporter to "
"confirm receipt within 24 hours of the incident being reported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:111
msgid "This acknowledgement will contain:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:113
msgid "Acknowledgement of the incident report"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:114
msgid "Next steps of the committee for responding to the incident"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:115
msgid ""
"Reminder of confidentiality policy regarding the report and parties involved"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:117
msgid ""
"All incident reports should be assessed if they require immediate response "
"and acted on accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:123
msgid "Incident Response Assessment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:125
msgid ""
"The committee will assess the incident and determine an appropriate "
"response. The assessment will be documented and retained in records. Here "
"are some guidelines for the process:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:129
msgid ""
"Review report documentation to determine the content and context of the "
"incident."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:132
msgid "Request additional information if needed from the reporter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:134
msgid "Determine if it occurred within the scope of the CoC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:135
msgid "Determine if it violated the CoC and specifically which part."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:136
msgid ""
"Consult documentation of past incidents for patterns of behavior (if "
"available and applicable)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:138
msgid ""
"Follow up with the reportee to get their view or any other additional "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:140
msgid ""
"Determine appropriate resolutions to the incident when all information has "
"been gathered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:142
msgid ""
"Notify the reporter of the resolution and request feedback. This may or may "
"not be used to reevaluate the resolution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:145
msgid ""
"The committee will aim to have a resolution agreed upon within two weeks of "
"receipt of the incident report. In the event that a resolution cannot be "
"determined within that time, the CoC committee will respond to the "
"reporter(s) with an updated and projected timeline for resolution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:153
msgid "Following Up With the Reportee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:155
msgid "When following up with the reportee, the committee will:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:157
msgid "Explain that an incident was reported that involves the reportee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:158
msgid ""
"In this explanation, the focus will be on the impact of their behavior, not "
"their intent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:160
msgid ""
"Reiterate the Code of Conduct and that their behavior may be deemed "
"inappropriate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:162
msgid "Give them the opportunity to state their view of the incident."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:163
msgid ""
"Explain the possible resolutions that may be enforced should the CoC "
"committee determine there is a breach."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:166
msgid ""
"The reportee will be given a week to respond with the option to request "
"additional time if needed and subject to approval of the CoC Committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:172
msgid "Resolutions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:174
msgid ""
"The committee should agree unanimously on a resolution. In the event that "
"the committee cannot reach a unanimous resolution, the LLVM Foundation Board "
"of Directors will help resolve the situation and determine if the resolution "
"can proceed without a unanimous vote."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:179
msgid ""
"When deciding on a resolution, the goal is to address the report in an "
"appropriate way, while also looking to prevent or reduce the risk of "
"continuing harm in the future. Any action deemed necessary by the committee "
"will be taken, but below is a list of possible resolutions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:184
msgid ""
"Taking no further action as the incident was determined not to be a "
"violation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:186
msgid ""
"A private verbal warning and/or reprimand from the committee to the "
"individual(s) involved and request to stop this behavior. This conversation "
"may happen in person, email, by phone, video chat, or IRC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:189
msgid ""
"Request that the reportee avoid any interaction with, and physical proximity "
"to, another person for the remainder of the event."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:191
msgid "Refusal of alcoholic beverage purchases by the reportee at LLVM events."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:192
msgid ""
"Ending a talk/tutorial/etc at an LLVM event early. See immediate response "
"checklist for further clarification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:194
msgid "Not publishing the video or slides of a talk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:195
msgid ""
"Not allowing a speaker to give (further) talks at LLVM events for a "
"specified amount of time or ever."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:197
msgid "Requiring that the reportee immediately leave an event and not return."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:198
msgid ""
"Immediately ending any volunteer responsibilities and privileges the "
"reportee holds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:200
msgid ""
"An imposed suspension (e.g., asking someone to \"take a week off\" from "
"mailing lists, bug tracker, IRC, Discord, repositories, or other "
"communication forms)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:203
msgid ""
"A permanent or temporary ban from some or all LLVM Project spaces (online or "
"in person)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:206
msgid ""
"Once a resolution is agreed upon, but before it is enacted, the committee "
"will contact the reporter and any other affected parties to explain the "
"proposed resolution. They will ask if this resolution is acceptable and must "
"note feedback for the record. However, the committee is not required to act "
"on this feedback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:215
msgid "Appeal Process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:217
msgid ""
"Any individual(s) determined to have violated the CoC have the right to "
"appeal a decision. An appeal can be made directly to the committee by "
"sending an email to conduct@llvm.org with subject line Code of Conduct "
"Incident Appeal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:221
msgid ""
"The email should include documentation related to the incident to support "
"the appeal. The said documentation may include, but does not have to be "
"limited to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:224
msgid "Information from the reportee justifying reasoning for the appeal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:225
msgid ""
"Statements from other individuals involved in the incident to support the "
"appeal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:228
msgid ""
"Appeals can be requested up to 30 days after a resolution has been "
"communicated to the individual(s). The committee will aim to evaluate "
"appeals within two weeks of receipt. In the event that appeal can not be "
"evaluated within that time, the CoC committee will respond with an updated "
"and projected timeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:233
msgid "Conflicts of Interest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:235
msgid ""
"Committee members should declare any conflicts of interest as soon as "
"possible and before any official committee meetings. This can mean being "
"friends with one of the involved parties, or anything else that may make it "
"harder to remain neutral."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:240
msgid ""
"A conflict of interest does not inherently mean the committee member can no "
"longer participate in the process, as that would make it very hard for the "
"team to act on reports involving well-known people in the community. "
"However, if a report concerns a team member or someone they work directly "
"with, they probably should not take part in the process. The team will "
"decide together on where to draw this line in individual cases. Where "
"possible, any conversations with offenders should not be done by people who "
"know them, as it can be very unpleasant for everyone involved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:249
msgid ""
"If a report is received concerning a committee member, that member must not "
"be involved in the response process. The rest of the committee will meet and "
"decide on the report without the reported committee member being present, "
"and will not share more information than they would have with a non-member. "
"If a member of the committee is found to have violated the CoC, they may no "
"longer be able to keep serving on the committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:257
msgid "Confidentiality"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:259
msgid ""
"All reports will be kept confidential with details shared only with the Code "
"of Conduct committee members. However, the Code of Conduct Committee will "
"always comply with law enforcement when directed. In the case that a CoC "
"committee member is involved in a report, the member will be asked to recuse "
"themselves from ongoing conversations, and they will not have access to "
"reports after the enforcement decision has been made."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:266
msgid ""
"In the event of a temporary suspension or ban, the appropriate people must "
"be notified of the ban in order to restrict access to infrastructure or "
"events. These individuals will only be notified of the person's name and the "
"restrictions imposed. They will be under a confidentiality clause and not "
"allowed to respond to questions regarding the ban and should direct all "
"questions to the CoC committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:276
msgid "Transparency Reports"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:278
msgid ""
"Lack of transparency in the outcomes of our Code of Conduct incidents leaves "
"our community without an understanding of how or if the organizers worked to "
"resolve incidents. The CoC committee should aim to publish transparency "
"reports, if reports are received, after major events (such as the LLVM "
"Developers' meetings) and on the following dates: Jan 15, April 15, July 15, "
"Oct 15."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:285
msgid "A transparency report consists of 2 parts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:287
msgid "An overview of the reports received, and resolutions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:288
msgid ""
"A more detailed summary of each reported incident and the resolution while "
"maintaining confidentiality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ResponseGuide.rst:291
msgid "These reports will be published on the LLVM website."
msgstr ""

